<p>
  Cropping removes the outer parts of an image to focus on a specific area, meet an aspect ratio requirement, or eliminate unwanted content. Here is how to crop any image for free — in your browser, no software needed.
</p>

<h2>When to Crop an Image</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Social media profile photos:</strong> Most platforms require a square (1:1) crop for profile pictures.</li>
  <li><strong>YouTube thumbnails:</strong> 16:9 aspect ratio is required — crop your photo to fit before uploading.</li>
  <li><strong>Remove unwanted borders:</strong> Scanned documents often have black or white borders. Crop them out for a clean result.</li>
  <li><strong>Focus on the subject:</strong> Tighten the composition by cropping out distracting background elements.</li>
  <li><strong>Print formats:</strong> Different print sizes (4×6, 5×7, 8×10) require different aspect ratios.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to Crop an Image Free Online</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open the <a href="/imagewonder/image-cropper">Image Cropper</a>.</li>
  <li>Drop your image or click to browse.</li>
  <li>Drag on the canvas to draw your crop selection.</li>
  <li>Or enter exact X, Y, width, height values in the number inputs.</li>
  <li>Select an aspect ratio preset if needed (1:1, 4:3, 16:9, 3:2).</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Crop & Download</strong>.</li>
</ol>

