<h2>Crop on iPhone (Built-in)</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open the photo in the <strong>Photos</strong> app.</li>
  <li>Tap <strong>Edit</strong> → crop icon (bottom right).</li>
  <li>Drag the corners to crop. Tap an aspect ratio icon for presets.</li>
  <li>Tap <strong>Done</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Crop on Android</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open the photo in <strong>Google Photos</strong>.</li>
  <li>Tap the edit pencil → <strong>Crop</strong>.</li>
  <li>Drag corners or select an aspect ratio preset.</li>
  <li>Tap <strong>Save copy</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Crop Tips</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Apply the Rule of Thirds: position your subject at one of the four intersection points of the grid, not dead center.</li>
  <li>Crop generously — you can always crop more later, but you cannot recover removed pixels.</li>
  <li>For print, crop to the exact aspect ratio of your print size before ordering.</li>
</ul>

